social_posts.post_text: @cookingdanny & I opened @mijo_nyc today and it was amazing , but we left a bit early as we had promised our son that we were going to go to a “color party” with his cousins, our only family here. It was our our first time at a Holi celebration  and this  was indeed the highlight of a very important and very awesome day! I am filled with joy and gratitude, hoping for a year filled with color, laughter and time together !

Sooo good to see my Chilte back to his silly, happy , full of energy self this morning after several days of feeling crappy and fighting  a virus that meant sleepless and scary nights.

Today is the first day of our 3rd anual CHOCOLATE DOUGHNUT FESTIVAL with @guittardchocolate @fanfandoughnuts and i am so excited! This year’s theme is childhood forever and whenever i think of mine, my sister @yaelagerson is always part of my memories. This doughnut is dedicated to her and called “hermanita” (little sister). One of her favorite desserts growing up was a raspberry tart with a condensed milk-white chocolate filling so I knew i wanted to recreate that. She is always quite stylish, gas a bold personality , is sweet and the most fun person I know so I tried to capture all those flavor and essence in this flavor. It’s a raspberry white chocolate glaze with a brown butter raspberry- cookie crumble and condensed milk. I wish she could be here to taste it but hope you all love it as much as I love her

Yesterday was the last day of our 3rd chocolate doughnut festival and it was amazing!! Creating something like this requires a lot of moving parts, planning and work . Doing it just a few weeks after opening @mijo_nyc with lots going on was a bit.. well.. crazy but it was worth it! Every year I try to pick a theme that people can relate or connect to somehow  no matter where they are from and  also reflect things I’m thinking about. This year’s theme  was childhood forever and it was really inspired by our son. The world 🌎 right now is frankly messed up and broken in so many ways but kids see life through a different lens. One that is filled with wonder, joy, imagination and often magic. Through these doughnuts, my hope was to bring a bot of that that we often forget about as adults.

It was a great festival and want to rhank the incredible staff that helped make it happen, @guittardchocolate for the delicious and beautiful chocolate that was the canvas for this, to all who participated in the contest, to @michelle.illo for the beautiful illustrations and artwork created for the festival, to @artexperimentos & @artshackbrooklyn for the awesome clay art that they created and to all who came , especially those who traveled from afar and patiently stood in line! We are filled with gratitude and joy. When we opened @fanfandoughnuts one our biggest and most important missions was to build community and we are so thanksgiving for the beautiful community that we feel proud to be part of. Thank you, thank you, thank you!!!

Yesterday, we celebrated our son’s birthday but also finished our piñata which has been a yearly tradition. He originaly wanted a purple giraffe (no idea why) and got some materials fir it but I started preparing it too late and knew I wouldn’t have time so he said maybe a sorcerer’s hat from Harry Potter and didn’t get to the store on time to get paint or paper. As of yesterday morning i only had the balloon covered in the paper layer and not fully dry but doing this together is an important tradition and didn’t want to have to go buy one so i came up with a loose idea and started working on it at 5 AM with whatever we had on hand. I was eager for him to wake up and when he did he was excited and on board with the idea! We made a bugs themed piñata and he decorated , cut , glued a lot of the bugs and carefully picked the leaves from our backyard. We had the best time and he was soooo excited. I gotta say, i feel very proud of our last minute idea and making it together will be a memory that i’ll hold dear to my heart always #itsthelittlethings 🐛 🦋 🐞 💕

A couple days ago @masienda won a James beard media award (check out their awesome documentary series on YouTube!) and it reminded me to share this video I’ve been meaning to post about how I like to cure my molcajetes (there are several ways) and by the way- huge congrats to them!! 

For those who may not know , a molcajete is a mortar and pestle made of fine-grained lava rock used for grinding spices and chiles, and preparing salsas & guacamole and found in most Mexican kitchen’s. Salsas definitely taste different and better in them in my opinion and the one from Masienda is honestly one of the nicest ones i’ve ever seen and you can even watch a video about how they make them on the website.

Anyways.. before you use it, you need to cure it and hope this little video helps but in case it wasn’t clear, here’s the gist of it:

-wash your molcajete with water and escopeta or scrub and dry
-add approximately 1/2 cup of uncooked white rice and a bit of coarse salt to the bowl. Using as much of the bowl’s surface area as possible, grind the rice into a rough powder rinse and repeat (you can put a towel underneath if you want to prevent scratching the surface 
- do this process until it’s almost clear (with no gray residues) and then grind a bit of chile with garlic . Grind & add rice &  salt again & rinse.
- Place inside a warm oven (300 F or so) to dry
- Cool completely 
-Now you are ready to make some delicious salsas!! 🌶️ 🥑 🌿

🥧This recipe comes from chef and entrepreneur @fanygerson. This pastry dough spans four generations of women in Fany’s family from her Ukrainian great-grandmother all the way to New York City. This cherished recipe serves as a reminder of Chef Fany’s childhood in her grandmother Ana’s kitchen in Mexico City.

My dad was all heart. He was kind, sweet, generous, brilliant, unique, honest, courageous, and just the most amazing human that shined like a star. He was a wonderful father, grandfather, friend, brother and son. He lived his life leading with love and touched countless people along the way, without most likely ever knowing the incredible impact he had on them. 

He was, and will continue to be the person I admire most in this world and feel so lucky and grateful that I got to be his daughter and to know him always felt like a privilege. He has inspired my siblings and I in countless ways and i  am certain the wonderful bond that exists between us is because of him. Family was everything to him.

He lived with boundless love, inspiring us all & taught us that attitude defines us, not our circumstances.

I am utterly heartbroken, and still in shock, but I am also filled with gratitude and love. Anytime something important happened in my life, good or bad, he was the first person I called & I always yearned to make him proud. I know that he will continue to guide us through and with the immense love that was Boris and hope that he knows and feels how deeply loved he was and will continue to be. I hope to live my life in many ways through his eyes - leading with kindness, grateful, hotizontal, loving and thoughtful. 

Pa, ya te extrañamos y nos haces muchísima falta. Gracias por todo!

Esta es una de mis fotos favoritas tuyas cuando me acompañaste a Oaxaca mientras hacía mi investigación del libro . Me encabta  la foto en si porque captura tu alegría , gran sonrisa y amo el sombrero, pero mas que nada por el momento que vivimos que representa uno de miles que podrían parecer insignificantes pero son todo! 

Espero que donde sea que estés, te acobije y acompañe el inmenso amor que te rodea y dejaste esparcido por el mundo, que sepas lo maravilloso que eres, que sientas la magia que  cosechaste con tu bondad y dulzura en el mundo, que descanses, estes en paz y que sigas brillando como siempre, para siempre…

Today, my dear aunt Sari, my dad’s older sister Sari, showed me how to make my Babi’s  pecan strudel. I had tried and loved it when i was a child and have  been wanting to learn this recipe for years, but for one reason or another we never found time. She joked that she hoped that  it would come out well and not like the chapter in “like water for chocolate” where everyone got sick from a dish one of the characters prepared when she was incredibly sad as we were and have been since my dad’s passing a little over a week ago. This was a special time we shared together where we laughed, cried and shared stories and silences remembering and loving my dad 💕. Ps. It was delicious and know my dad would’ve loved it!

Hace un mes que te fuiste de este mundo.. necesito hablar contigo, abrazarte y la verdad me siento perdida sin ti.  Siento como una tela delgada  gris invisible a mi alrededor que no me permite ver claramente y a veces pesa tanto que me quita el aire. Te extraño tanto tanto y me duele . A la vez, como siempre, me siento inmensamente agradecida de haber tenido un papa’ tan maravilloso  y tan presente. Esta foto es de mis favoritas no solo por la foto en si, sino por el momento. En esa ocasión cruzamos el puente de Brooklyn como lo hicimos muchas veces , pero fue después de que habías dejado de poder caminar un tiempo y finalmente podías nuevamente. Cruzamos lenta y pausadamente valorando  cada paso e instante. Siempre luchaste, incluso hasta el final de tu vida, pero siempre  por y con amor por ti, por nosotros , por un mundo mas justo , mas horizontal y mas noble. Un ejemplo para todos en incontables maneras y eres la persona que mas  admiro en mi vida. Todas las noches le pregunto a Gael si quisiera preguntarte o decirte algo y casi siempre contesta una de dos cosas : “Abuelo Boris ya quiero que regreses. Te quiero ver!”
y “te amo abuelo Boris” - eso  lo resume todo. Te busco y no te encuentro pero donde sea que estés, espero que sientas el inmenso amor que te rodea y que te acompañe siempre. Gracias infinitas papi, te amo.

I made this special bread earlier today for my dad’s ofrenda. I lovingly decorated it with sugar until the tears just starting pouring and I couldn’t anymore. I was going to start again bit decide it to leave it as is… This pan de muerto is inspired by the ones in Oaxaca  made with anise seed and canela just like the ones we make @lanewyorkina . Made with love, for love, for my pa.

Cooking and baking don’t change hard times but I always find it helps and find some comfort. If you are looking for something new to make you can try out this puerquito/marranitos. For those unfamiliar, it’s a classic recipe from Mexico made with piloncillo, an unrefined sugar with molassy taste. The texture between soft & crunchy and very distinctive, perfect for fall . You can check out this special recipe I made for @kingarthurbaking on their website for their pan dulce campaign. Hope you make it and share some pics!! These cookies always make me smile 😊

Couple minutes before i took this pic my Chilte said “quiero decirte algo - amo cocinar contigo mami” (“i want to tell you something - i love cooking with you” ) and i melted into a puddle. Not sure if he knows but these little moments mean the world 🌎.

social_posts.post_text: Feeling hungry or craving  some yummy Mexican antojitos?  We got you covered @mijo_nyc @pier57.nyc and look forward to welcoming you!

Seven years ago today, under a beautiful chuppah surrounded by love, my sweet @cookingdanny and I got married ! It was a magical week long celebration in Mexico filled with love, laughter, family, friends , great food, music and pure joy. I look back at that moment and feel those emotions multiplied with our sweet boy. Your dad used to say he loved our relationship because he always heard us laugh a lot together and thankfully we still are jaja. Life has thrown us difficult moments and circumstances, but you are truly my best friend and accomplice . We  became instant friends the moment we met & I am grateful for you every day! I am also grateful my dad got to know you and know he loved you deeply and know he was like a father figure to you as well. He would’ve been the first to call to congratulate us and know his blessings will continue to give us strength and love through life. Here’s toasting for many many more years of laughter, love, learnings, discoveries, color , adventure and joy

Introducing the CARDOZ LEGACY DIWALI DOUGHNUT BOX! @cardozlegacy & @fanfandoughnuts are thrilled to share this masala-spiced doughnut in celebration of Barkha Cardoz's upcoming book, WITH LOVE & MASALAS! The four doughnuts feature Cardoz Legacy's signature masalas and (brand new!) Masala Chai, made into sweet deliciousness in doughnut form.

🍩 Garam Masala with Caramelized White Chocolate and Raspberry Dust 
🍩 Chaat Masala with Passion Fruit, Citrus Glaze, and Chocolate Masala Drizzle 
🍩 Kashmiri Masala with Apple-Quince Caramel 
🍩 Masala Chai with Chai Diplomat Cream and Coffee Sugar 

Preorder the collection online or get them individually in-store from@the 11th-19th where you can also pick up a copy of the new book. Come to the shop between 11 a.m. and 12 p.m. on Saturday the 11th, and Barkha will sign your copy for you! 

A portion of the proceeds from this collab will go to The Floyd Cardoz Scholarship at the Welcomgroup Graduate School of Hotel Administration. Learn more at www.CardozLegacy.com/With-Love-And-Masalas.

@fanfandoughnuts we make a Belgian style hot chocolate. It’s thick but not overly rich and made with a blend of bittersweet and a touch of milk chocolate. We top it with a torched homemade marshmallow and doughnut croutons. Thank you @thecarboholic for the kind words and ❤️!

Check out our Mexican inspired thanksgiving feast @mijo_nyc !! This year we are thrilled to bring back this special menu we created in the pandemic. Roasted “al pastor” chicken, turkey - house made mole tamales, butternut squash with cilantro pepitas pesto, charred garlic broccoli with guajillo , delicious pies & ice cream from @lanewyorkina and lots more!! Pre- order directly @mijo_nyc website. Let us take care of the cooking so you have more tike to enjoy yourselves 🍨 🥧 🌶️ 💕

🎉 Our collab box with @tomcolicchio is back, and we are sooooo excited! Preorders are on our website but we’ll also have some extras starting Monday and we’ll be open Thanksgiving day till 1PM. These doughnuts bring Thanksgiving flavors to life! Each box features:
- Pecan pie filled with vanilla diplomat
- Pumpkin cheesecake
- Cranberry-orange glazed braid
- Sweet potato-meringue
- Brown butter cinnamon bun
Get yours before they're gone! 🍩✨
Sooooo excited for this sufganiyot class I’ll be teaching with The Nosher. Yead over the @jewishfood  to get tickets for this very gun , very delicious virtual class 🍓 🍩

These last couple of months have been emotionally tough but had the chance to spend a few days visiting my brother @pger & @marianatapia___ and has some much needed quality time with my @cookingdanny & our sweet Chilte. I love chicago and had some fantastic food and incredibly welcoming hospitality @publicanbread @lobapastry @galit_restaurant @kasamachicago & @avecchicago - thank you all for everything!! Most of all it’s the time together that means everything and while hardships and the heavy feelings don’t disappear, I am grateful these moments and they help heal a bit. ❤️

🎉 sooo excited to share this year’s Sufganiyot Collection Box @fanfandoughnuts Dive into unique flavors like homemade strawberry jam, raspberry cheesecake, mocha praline & dulce de leche, mango-vanilla, our special latke collab with @pastryschiff , and the irresistible passion meringue. Pre-order now through our website for December 6th-15th or snag limited quantities in-store! This year,  everything feels quite heavy but trying to bring some joy and comfort through these in a small way . 💕

Over the weekend I was part of the most beautiful bunch put together by @jewishfoodsociety  and took lots of doughnut from @fanfandoughnuts and then headed to @thegoodbatch cookie fest @pier57 and got to try some  very delicious cookie contest @kalnyc as they invited me to participate as a judge this year. All in all these food events felt like an enormous community hug . Got to see so many people i love and admire and honestly really needed it.

This year, @cookingdanny and I created a special holiday menu @mijo_nyc that highlights some of the special things we did during the pandemic when we had EL newyorkino plus a couple other favorites. Some of these dishes are - romeritos con mole , fresh cod cafes “a la Vizcaina”, charred  carrots 🥕 with goat cheese and cilantro, pomegranate short rib and cochinita pibil tamales to name a few .. and of course LOTS of dessert options from @lanewyorkina. Menu is available from the 20th-31st and you can  preorder at www.mijo.nyc

Chocoflan , also known as flan imposible is one of my favorite desserts to make and eat! The chocolate cake and flan layers flip during baking and it has a cajeta caramel- definitely a celebratory dessert! We are making is as one of the special desserts for our holiday menu @mijo_nyc and you can order directly through the website. It’s a crowd pleaser for sure!

Our hot chocolate @fanfandoughnuts ! Belgian style inspired by a recipe by @davidlebovitz topped with doughnut croutons and homemade toasted marshmallow. Have you tried it yet? Ps. My Chilte chose the song 🎵 for the reel and think it’s kind of perfect for it jeje 🤩

Help me wish my sweet, kind, fun , loving @cookingdanny a very happy birthday !!! Here’s toasting to many more celebrations together for years to come!!! Every day when I wake up , I feel so grateful and lucky that we met and that our sweet Chilte gets to have such an amazing dad to learn from, be silly, cook, discover, wonder, cuddle and play with. Te amo mi güero 💕

On the 6th of January, we celebrate 3 kings day in Mexico and the ROSCA de REYES take center stage! You can preorder through @lanewyorkina website for both local  orders and through @goldbelly to get it delivered straight yo your fooras we have  nationwide delivery 🚚.!!! We have 2 kinds - the classic one scented with orange blossom and zest filled with candied fruit and a sugary vanilla topping. The other is our signature black and white with a Mexican  chocolate filling and topped with  buttery and sugary vanilla and chocolate toppings which is like the concha toppings ;). Whoever gets the little baby figurine inside has to make or bring tamales for Día de la Candelaria, Candlemas, celebrates on Feb 2nd

As this year comes to an end,  I try to acknowledge and celebrate many wonderful things that happened this year but honestly I am just deeply  sad and  really miss my dad. I look at photos and it hurts, but I also try to hold on to all the joy that he brought to my life. Me and my siblings are so fortunate to have had a father that was truly remarkable- so loving, present, kind, thoughtful , generous, brilliant and all heart.

This is one of my favorite photos as it’s one of my favorite memories . Every time he came to NY , we crossed the Brooklyn Bridge. That was challenging for many years, as he had different health issues, but always with his incredibly positive attitude and beautiful smile. This was the first time we crossed it with my son and just a few days ago, I walked  it with Manuel, his life partner but without him there for the first time. I will cherish this memory as all the countless ones we had together and for that and for him, I am beyond grateful.

My son told me a couple night ago that the stars are kisses that people that have passed away are sending us, and loved that,  so I am hoping for lots of starry nights! 

I am toasting to you pa and know that we feel blessed for the many years we got to celebrate life with you and hope you know how deeply you are loved and how much we all miss you.

Our SPECIAL HOLIDAY BAKER’S DOZEN @fanfandoughnuts has been so fun and wonderful to create with so many incredible chefs, creators and friends. As many of you know , we were broken into on Christmas day and though luckily and thankfully no one was hurt (which is the most important thing !) but we did loose 10 days worth of cash sales so we decided to extend it through January 15th as we also know a lot people reached out to see if we could have it after the new year and we’ll continue to have some of the flavors in rotation at the shop sold individually ;)

My dear friend and incredibly talented artist and art educator @leairbag made this amulet for me/us to protect our shop!!!! Of course I cried sooo much when she told me  and just had no words.

Over the years we’ve had people that have stolen our recipes, copied us ,  have tried to intimidate us, threaten us vandalize and honestly just a lot for a small business  and all the people behind it. @fanfandoughnuts is a business that is built on love, respect, honesty, hard work , creativity and community . A few weeks ago she came to visit and i was photographing the cardamom-rose special i created in collaboration with @chefchintan so when she heard we were robbed on Christmas day she created this incredible amulet inspired by that doughnut and one of Gertrude Stein’s  poems so she celled it “a rose is a tose is a rose”
It’s made with paper mache and mixed media. Amongst many of the wonderful things she does , are some beautiful ceramic pieces crafted with kids @artshackbrooklyn and sold at our shop. All the money goes directly to their scholarship programing. 

I am truly touched! Isn’t she and this amulet simply amazing?!
Mom, cookbook author, chef/founder @lanewyorkina, @fanfandoughnuts & @mijo_nyc. Cookbook author, James Beard nominee & proud Mexican
